 How to Setup django project :

  => create and activate ENV(Virtual Environment)(already built-in python 3.3+)

    how to check run in cmd = python -m venv --help

  we create it si that the every project created have their package seperated
  ENV is just like a room and and each project store their package on their room so that it 
  prevent collapse and our system is like a house and we create room using ENV
                               OR
  “Virtual Environments” allow Python packages to be installed in an isolated location for a particular application, rather than being installed globally.

  run this command to create venv in you root project folder => python -m venv venv
  => and activate this => using command venv\Scripts\activate
  now create project => django-admin startproject myproject
  => Virtual environment is usually created inside the project directory but separate from the project code.